ou're wrong. 22600:19:29.950 --> 00:19:32.780I do want to escape too. 22700:19:32.950 --> 00:19:33.970I'm so very tired of it all.I've struggled for food and for money. 22800:19:35.120 --> 00:19:36.640I've weeded and hoed and picked cottonuntil I can't stand it another minute. 22900:19:37.120 --> 00:19:38.090I tell you, Ashley, the South is dead.It's dead. 23000:19:39.660 --> 00:19:41.280The Yankees and the carpetbaggershave got it and there's nothing left for us. 23100:19:41.460 --> 00:19:44.450Oh, Ashley... 23200:19:44.630 --> 00:19:46.750...let's run away. 23300:19:46.830 --> 00:19:50.360We'd go to Mexico. 23400:19:50.500 --> 00:19:51.970They want officers in the Mexican Army.We could be so happy there. 23500:19:52.040 --> 00:19:53.940I'd work for you, I'd do anything for you.You know you don't love Melanie. 23600:19:54.000 --> 00:19:56.470You told me you loved methat day at Twelve Oaks. 23700:19:56.540 --> 00:19:59.510And anyway, Melanie can't.... 23800:19:59.580 --> 00:20:02.810Dr. Meade told me she couldn't haveany more children and I could give you-- 23900:20:02.880 --> 00:20:05.580Can't we ever forgetthat day at Twelve Oaks? 24000:20:05.880 --> 00:20:07.370Do you think I could ever forget it?Have you forgotten it? 24100:20:07.450 --> 00:20:09.080Can you honestly say you don't love me? 24200:20:09.150 --> 00:20:12.090-No. I don't love you.-It's a lie! 24300:20:12.160 --> 00:20:15.610Even if it is, do you think I'd leave Melanieand the baby, break Melanie's heart? 24400:20:16.160 --> 00:20:18.220You couldn't leaveyour father and the girls. 24500:20:18.290 --> 00:20:20.690I could leave them. I'm sick of them.I'm tired of them. 24600:20:21.260 --> 00:20:24.760Yes, you're sick and tired.That's why you're talking this way. 24700:20:24.830 --> 00:20:26.430You've carried the load for all of us... 24800:20:26.500 --> 00:20:28.770...but from now on I'm going to bemore help to you, I promise. 24900:20:28.840 --> 00:20:31.310There's only one way you can help me. 25000:20:31.570 --> 00:20:33.600Take me away. 25100:20:33.680 --> 00:20:35.940There's nothing to keep us here. 25200:20:36.010 --> 00:20:38.570Nothing. 25300:20:38.650 --> 00:20:42.350Nothing except honor. 25400:20:42.420 --> 00:20:43.820Oh, please, Scarlett. 25500:20:44.290 --> 00:20:45.550Please, dear, you mustn't cry. 25600:20:46.060 --> 00:20:48.750You mustn't. 25700:20:48.830 --> 00:20:50.160Please, my brave dear, you mustn't plead. 25800:20:50.230 --> 00:20:52.720You do love me, you do love me. 25900:20:53.160 --> 00:20:55.930-Say it, say it.-Don't, don't. 26000:20:56.030 --> 00:20:58.230You love me, you love me. 26100:20:58.300 --> 00:21:01.900We won't do this, I tell you.It won't happen again. 26200:21:02.310 --> 00:21:05.100I'm going to take Melanieand the baby, and go. 26300:21:05.640 --> 00:21:07.630Say it, you love me. 26400:21:07.940 --> 00:21:10.540All right, I'll say it.I love your courage and your stubbornness. 26500:21:10.680 --> 00:21:13.740So much that I could have forgottenthe best wife a man ever had. 26600:21:13.820 --> 00:21:17.150But, Scarlett, I'm not going to forget her. 26700:21:17.220 --> 00:21:18.740Then there's nothing left for me. 26800:21:18.820 --> 00:21:19.850Nothing to fight for. 26900:21:19.920 --> 00:21:22.120Nothing to live for. 27000:21:22.190 --> 00:21:23.560Yes, there is something. 27100:21:23.630 --> 00:21:25.590Something you love better than me... 27200:21:25.660 --> 00:21:27.930...though you may not know it. 27300:21:28.100 --> 00:21:32.030Tara! 27400:21:32.370 --> 00:21:35.530Yes, l... 27500:21:41.110 --> 00:21:42.840...l still have this. 27600:21:42.980 --> 00:21:43.950You needn't go. 27700:21:44.010 --> 00:21:46.040I won't have you all starve simplybecause I threw myself at your head. 27800:21:46.420 --> 00:21:47.610It won't happen again. 27900:21:47.720 --> 00:21:51.740-Why, it's Emmy Slattery.-Yes, ma'am, it's me. 28000:21:51.820 --> 00:21:53.950Stop! 28100:21:58.800 --> 00:22:02.030You haven't forgotten your old overseer,have you? 28200:22:02.100 --> 00:22:03.160Well, Emmy's Mrs. Wilkerson now. 28300:22:03.530 --> 00:22:05.330Get off those steps, you trashy wench!Get off this land! 28400:22:05.700 --> 00:22:07.260You can't speak that way to my wife. 28500:22:07.340 --> 00:22:09.860Wife! High time you made her your wife. 28600:22:09.940 --> 00:22:12.270Who baptized your other bratsafter you killed my mother? 28700:22:12.340 --> 00:22:15.610We came out here to pay a friendly calland talk a little business with old friends. 28800:22:15.680 --> 00:22:16.700Friends! When were we ever friendswith the likes of you? 28900:22:16.880 --> 00:22:21.110Still high and mighty, ain't you?Well, I know all about you. 29000:22:21.680 --> 00:22:24.180I know your father's turned idiot. 29100:22:27.790 --> 00:22:30.380You can't pay your taxes. 29200:22:36.130 --> 00:22:37.660And I come hereto offer to buy the place from you... 29300:22:37.830 --> 00:22:38.930...to make you a right good offer. 29400:22:39.040 --> 00:22:40.020Emmy's had a hankerin' to live here. 29500:22:41.770 --> 00:22:43.900Get off this place, you dirty Yankee. 29600:22:44.340 --> 00:22:46.770You high-flyin' lrish will find outwho's runnin' things around here... 29700:22:48.180 --> 00:22:50.580...when you get sold out for taxes. 29800:22:50.650 --> 00:22:52.240I'll buy this place lock, stock and barreland I'll live in it. 29900:22:52.320 --> 00:22:53.370But I'll wait for the sheriff's sale. 30000:22:53.780 --> 00:22:55.270That's all of Tara you'll ever get! 30100:22:55.350 --> 00:22:56.880You'll be sorry for that. 30200:22:57.520 --> 00:23:01.510We'll be back! 30300:23:01.660 --> 00:23:03.820I'll show you who the owner of Tara is. 30400:23:04.560 --> 00:23:05.650Pa, come back! 30500:23:05.730 --> 00:23:08.990Pa, come back! 30600:23:09.130 --> 00:23:11.730Pa! 30700:23:12.300 --> 00:23:14.770Yankee coward! 30800:23:15.770 --> 00:23:17.070Pa! 30900:23:17.770 --> 00:23:20.500Lordsy, Miss Scarlett.That's Mr. Gerald's watch. 31000:23:21.280 --> 00:23:22.400You take it. It's for you.Pa'd want you to have it. 31100:23:27.520 --> 00:23:29.250You ain't got no business partin'from this watch now, Miss Scarlett. 31200:23:29.320 --> 00:23:31.790You needs all your valuablesto sell for that tax money. 31300:23:33.190 --> 00:23:34.280Do you think I'd sell Pa's watch? 31400:23:34.360 --> 00:23:36.760And don't cry. 31500:23:39.000 --> 00:23:40.190I can stand everybody's tears but yours. 31600:23:43.500 --> 00:23:46.300Oh, Mammy, Mammy. 31700:23:47.900 --> 00:23:49.570You been brave so long, Miss Scarlett,you just gotta go on bein' brave. 31800:23:50.110 --> 00:23:51.330Think about your pa like he used to be. 31900:23:51.570 --> 00:23:52.700I can't think about Pa. 32000:23:52.880 --> 00:23:55.000I can't think of anything but that $300. 32100:24:02.320 --> 00:24:03.340Ain't no good thinkin' about that,Miss Scarlett. 32200:24:04.890 --> 00:24:05.880Ain't nobody got that much money. 32300:24:07.490 --> 00:24:09.890Nobody but Yankees and scalawags gotthat much money now. 32400:24:13.300 --> 00:24:16.090Rhett! 32500:24:16.370 --> 00:24:18.700Who that? A Yankee? 32600:24:18.770 --> 00:24:22.700Oh, Mammy, I'm so thin and pale and... 32700:24:22.770 --> 00:24:26.210...l haven't any clothes. 32800:24:26.280 --> 00:24:30.140Scoot up to the attic and get downMa's old box of dress patterns. 32900:24:30.310 --> 00:24:31.910What you up to with Miss Ellen's portieres? 33000:24:31.980 --> 00:24:34.580You'll make me a new dress. 33100:24:34.720 --> 00:24:36.450Not with Miss Ellen's portieres.Not while I got breath in me. 33200:24:36.690 --> 00:24:38.880Great balls of fire!They're my portieres now. 33300:24:38.960 --> 00:24:40.250I'm going to Atlanta for that $300and I've got to go looking like a queen. 33400:24:40.320 --> 00:24:42.760-Who goin' to Atlanta with you?-I'm going alone. 33500:24:42.830 --> 00:24:43.990That's what you think.I's goin' to Atlanta with you. 33600:24:45.060 --> 00:24:47.830With you and that new dress. 33700:24:48.000 --> 00:24:49.620Now, Mammy, darling. 33800:24:49.700 --> 00:24:52.670No use to try to sweet-talk me,Miss Scarlett. 33900:24:52.740 --> 00:24:53.860I's knowed you since I putthe first pair of diapers on you. 34000:25:45.220 --> 00:25:47.750I said I's goin' to Atlanta with you,and goin' I is. 34100:25:47.820 --> 00:25:50.590Kings and traes, huh?Too good for me, Major! 34200:25:50.660 --> 00:25:52.090Pity we couldn't have fought the war outin a poker game. 34300:25:52.160 --> 00:25:54.960You'd have done better than General Grantwith far less effort. 34400:25:55.030 --> 00:25:55.960What is it, Corporal? 34500:25:56.030 --> 00:25:58.630Sir, there's a lady to see Captain Butler.Says she's his sister. 34600:25:59.070 --> 00:26:03.230Another sister? 34700:26:03.410 --> 00:26:05.770This is a jail, not a harem, Captain Butler. 34800:26:05.840 --> 00:26:07.570No, Major, she ain't one of those. 34900:26:07.640 --> 00:26:11.270This one's got her mammy with her. 35000:26:12.320 --> 00:26:13.750She has? 35100:26:13.820 --> 00:26:15.440I'd like to see this one, Major,without her mammy. 35200:26:15.520 --> 00:26:17.320Let's see, my losses for the afternooncome to what? 35300:26:17.390 --> 00:26:19.320Three hundred and forty. 35400:26:19.390 --> 00:26:21.320My debts do mount up, don't they, Major? 35500:26:21.390 --> 00:26:23.720All right, Corporal. 35600:26:23.860 --> 00:26:26.020Show Captain Butler's sister to his cell. 35700:26:26.200 --> 00:26:29.630Thank you, Major. Excuse me, gentlemen. 35800:26:30.570 --> 00:26:33.900It's hard to be strict with a manwho loses money so pleasantly. 35900:26:33.970 --> 00:26:35.600-Rhett!-Scarlett! 36000:26:35.670 --> 00:26:37.570My dear little sister. 36100:26:37.640 --> 00:26:41.080It's all right, Corporal.My sister has brought me no files or saws. 36200:26:41.210 --> 00:26:45.200Can I really kiss you now? 36300:26:45.280 --> 00:26:46.750On the forehead like a good brother. 36400:26:46.820 --> 00:26:50.840No, thanks.I'll wait and hope for better things. 36500:26:50.990 --> 00:26:53.050Oh, Rhett, I was so distressedwhen I heard you were in jail. 36600:26:53.590 --> 00:26:56.150I simply couldn't sleep for thinking. 36700:26:56.230 --> 00:26:57.620It's not true, they're going to hang you? 36800:26:57.760 --> 00:27:00.590Would you be sorry? 36900:27:00.660 --> 00:27:02.600-Oh, Rhett!-Well, don't worry, yet. 37000:27:02.670 --> 00:27:05.900They have plottedsome charge against me... 37100:27:05.970 --> 00:27:08.800...but they're really after my money. 37200:27:08.870 --> 00:27:10.070They think I made offwith the Confederate Treasury. 37300:27:10.140 --> 00:27:13.200Well, did you? 37400:27:13.280 --> 00:27:15.570What a leading question. 37500:27:15.650 --> 00:27:18.480But let's not talkabout sordid things like money. 37600:27:18.550 --> 00:27:21.880How good of you to come and see me.And how pretty you look. 37700:27:22.080 --> 00:27:25.610Oh, Rhett, how you do run on,teasing a country girl like me. 37800:27:25.720 --> 00:27:27.250Thank heavens you're not in rags.I'm tired of seeing women in rags. 37900:27:27.320 --> 00:27:29.620Turn around. 38000:27:29.790 --> 00:27:32.590Marvelous! You look good enough to eat.And prosperous, too. 38100:27:32.660 --> 00:27:36.890Thank you, I've been doing very well. 38200:27:41.340 --> 00:27:44.310Everybody's doing well at Tara, only... 38300:27:46.110 --> 00:27:48.840...l got so bored I just thoughtI'd treat myself to a visit to town. 38400:27:48.910 --> 00:27:52.210You're a heartless creature.But that's part of your charm. 38500:27:52.750 --> 00:27:54.110You know you've got more charmthan the law allows. 38600:28:01.090 --> 00:28:04.620Now I didn't come hereto talk silliness about me, Rhett. 38700:28:04.690 --> 00:28:06.490I came because I was so miserableat the thought of you in trouble. 38800:28:06.560 --> 00:28:07.720I was mad at you the night you left meon the road to Tara... 38900:28:07.800 --> 00:28:10.700...and I still haven't forgiven you. 39000:28:10.770 --> 00:28:11.730Oh, Scarlett, don't say that. 39100:28:11.870 --> 00:28:13.390Well, I must admit I might not be alive,now, only for you. 39200:28:13.470 --> 00:28:14.990And when I think of myselfwith everything I could possibly hope for... 39300:28:15.070 --> 00:28:17.010...and not a care in the world,and you here in this horrid jail... 39400:28:17.070 --> 00:28:18.370...and not even a human jail, Rhett,a horse jail. 39500:28:18.440 --> 00:28:20.970Oh, listen to me tryingto make jokes when... 39600:28:21.040 --> 00:28:23.880...when I really want to cry. 39700:28:24.180 --> 00:28:26.610In a minute I shall cry. 39800:28:26.680 --> 00:28:28.780Scarlett, can it be possible that.... 39900:28:41.530 --> 00:28:42.620Can what be possible, Rhett? 40000:28:50.210 --> 00:28:51.760That you've grown a woman's heart,a real woman's heart? 40100:28:52.340 --> 00:28:53.400I have, Rhett. I know I have. 40200:28:55.240 --> 00:28:57.440You know, it's worth being in jailjust to hear you say that. 40300:29:02.590 --> 00:29:04.280It's well worth it. 40400:29:06.320 --> 00:29:09.350You can drop the moonlightand magnolias, Scarlett. 40500:29:10.660 --> 00:29:12.690So things have been going wellat Tara, have they? 40600:29:13.100 --> 00:29:15.460What have you done with your hands? 40700:29:16.130 --> 00:29:17.290I went riding last weekwithout my gloves. 40800:29:17.670 --> 00:29:18.690These don't belong to a lady.You've worked with them like a field hand. 40900:29:18.770 --> 00:29:20.240Why did you lie? What are you up to? 41000:29:22.570 --> 00:29:26.230In another minute I'd have believedyou cared something. 41100:29:26.310 --> 00:29:28.710But I do care. 41200:29:28.780 --> 00:29:30.410Suppose we get down to the truth. 41300:29:30.480 --> 00:29:33.280You want something from me badly enoughto put on quite a show in your velvets. 41400:29:33.350 --> 00:29:36.980What is it? Money? 41500:29:37.090 --> 00:29:41.250I want $300 to pay the taxes on Tara. 41600:29:41.660 --> 00:29:43.780I did lie to youwhen I said everything was all right. 41700:29:45.030 --> 00:29:46.150Things are just as bad as they possiblycould be. And you've got millions, Rhett. 41800:29:46.730 --> 00:29:47.860What collateral are you offering? 41900:29:49.300 --> 00:29:52.170-My earbobs.-Not interested. 42000:29:54.000 --> 00:29:55.660-A mortgage on Tara.-What would I do with a farm? 42100:29:56.010 --> 00:29:58.240You wouldn't lose.I'd pay you back out of next year's cotton. 42200:29:58.370 --> 00:29:59.900Not good enough.Have you nothing better? 42300:30:00.140 --> 00:30:02.510You once said you loved me. 42400:30:02.580 --> 00:30:05.710If you still love me, Rhett.... 42500:30:06.620 --> 00:30:08.670You haven't forgottenthat I'm not a marrying man. 42600:30:09.490 --> 00:30:11.080No, I haven't forgotten. 42700:30:11.150 --> 00:30:12.480You're not worth $300. 42800:30:12.560 --> 00:30:14.990You'll never mean anythingbut misery to any man. 42900:30:15.160 --> 00:30:16.590Go on, insult me. 43000:30:16.730 --> 00:30:18.190I don't care what you say,only give me the money. 43100:30:18.590 --> 00:30:21.320I won't let Tara go. I can't let it gowhile there's a breath left in my body. 43200:30:21.630 --> 00:30:23.500Oh, Rhett. 43300:30:23.730 --> 00:30:25.360Won't you please give me the money? 43400:30:25.870 --> 00:30:28.390I couldn't give you the moneyif I wanted to. 43500:30:28.570 --> 00:30:31.040My funds are in Liverpool, not in Atlanta. 43600:30:31.110 --> 00:30:32.770If I tried drawing a draft, the Yankees'd beon me like a duck on a June bug. 43700:30:32.840 --> 00:30:36.070So you see, my dear,you've abased yourself to no purpose. 43800:30:36.310 --> 00:30:38.340Here, here, here, stop it! 43900:30:38.410 --> 00:30:42.210Want the Yankees to see you like this? 44000:30:42.280 --> 00:30:43.770Take your hands off me, you skunk. 44100:30:43.850 --> 00:30:45.580You knew what I was going to saybefore I started. 44200:30:45.650 --> 00:30:48.450You knew you wouldn't lend me the moneyand yet you let me go on. 44300:30:48.520 --> 00:30:50.860I enjoyed hearing what you had to say. 44400:30:50.930 --> 00:30:54.450Cheer up. You can come to my hangingand I'll remember you in my will. 44500:30:55.060 --> 00:30:58.360I'll come to your hanging.The only thing I'm afraid of... 44600:31:25.360 --> 00:31:27.230...is that they won't hang you in timeto pay the taxes on Tara. 44700:31:27.830 --> 00:31:31.230Tell him Belle Watlin'. 44800:31:31.530 --> 00:31:33.700Where you been lately?Thought you deserted Captain Butler. 44900:31:33.900 --> 00:31:36.100Oh, I keep myself occupied. Help me out. 45000:31:36.170 --> 00:31:38.730Who that? I ain't never see'd hairthat color before in my life. 45100:31:39.340 --> 00:31:40.430Does you know a dyed-hair woman? 45200:31:40.510 --> 00:31:42.640I wish I did know that one.She'd get my money for me. 45300:31:43.110 --> 00:31:44.940No matter what they done to youin that jail... 45400:31:45.010 --> 00:31:46.740...they didn't do no morethan you deserve... 45500:31:46.820 --> 00:31:49.840...for visitin' white trash in a jail! 45600:31:49.920 --> 00:31:53.360Fresh and green. 45700:31:53.420 --> 00:31:56.260Right off the farm. 45800:31:56.330 --> 00:32:00.590Hey, what are you doin' tonight, Susy? 45900:32:00.830 --> 00:32:02.300That's one of them Georgia peaches. 46000:32:02.500 --> 00:32:05.130There's nothing like that in Ohio. 46100:32:06.670 --> 00:32:09.660-You know what we're going to do?-What? 46200:32:12.010 --> 00:32:16.000We're going to give every last one of you40 acres and a mule! 46300:32:16.080 --> 00:32:17.740-And a mule?-Forty acres and a mule! 46400:32:17.810 --> 00:32:20.580Gee! 46500:32:20.680 --> 00:32:22.950'Cause we're your friends... 46600:32:23.020 --> 00:32:24.880...and you're gonna become voters... 46700:32:24.950 --> 00:32:27.050...and you're gonna votelike your friends do! 46800:32:27.120 --> 00:32:28.750What's your hurry, sister? 46900:32:28.820 --> 00:32:31.880What's come over this here town? 47000:32:32.060 --> 00:32:34.930Yankees have come over it!Same as they've come over all of us. 47100:32:35.000 --> 00:32:37.190Out of our way, trash! 47200:32:45.840 --> 00:32:48.810Get out of the way here. 47300:33:00.490 --> 00:33:01.890Get away! Go on! 47400:33:04.990 --> 00:33:06.150Surely it can't be Miss Scarlett! 47500:33:06.360 --> 00:33:09.660-Why Frank Kennedy!-And Mammy! 47600:33:09.730 --> 00:33:12.330It sure is good to see home folks. 47700:33:12.400 --> 00:33:14.770I didn't know you were in Atlanta. 47800:33:14.870 --> 00:33:16.390I didn't know you were. 47900:33:16.470 --> 00:33:17.530Didn't Miss Suellen tell youabout my store? 48000:33:21.840 --> 00:33:24.240Did she? I don't remember.Have you a store? 48100:33:24.650 --> 00:33:26.270Won't you come in, and look around a bit? 48200:33:26.780 --> 00:33:28.720I don't suppose it looks like muchto a lady, but... 48300:33:28.850 --> 00:33:30.840...l can't help being proud of it. 48400:33:31.020 --> 00:33:35.420You're not making money? 48500:33:35.560 --> 00:33:37.860Well, I can't complain.In fact, I'm mighty encouraged. 48600:33:37.930 --> 00:33:41.390Folks tell me I'm just a born merchant. 48700:33:41.460 --> 00:33:45.330It won't be long nowbefore Miss Suellen and I can marry. 48800:33:45.500 --> 00:33:47.030Are you doing as well as all that? 48900:33:47.570 --> 00:33:48.830Yes, I am, Miss Scarlett. 49000:33:48.940 --> 00:33:51.770I'm no millionaire yet... 49100:33:57.550 --> 00:33:59.510...but I've cleared $1,000 already. 49200:34:00.120 --> 00:34:02.380And lumber too. 49300:34:02.820 --> 00:34:04.080Well... 49400:34:04.150 --> 00:34:06.590...that's only a sideline. 49500:34:07.090 --> 00:34:09.060A sideline, Frank? 49600:34:09.120 --> 00:34:10.850With all the good Georgia pine aroundAtlanta and all this building going on? 49700:34:12.530 --> 00:34:14.020Well, all that takes money, Miss Scarlett... 49800:34:14.100 --> 00:34:15.150...and I've got to be thinkingabout buying a home. 49900:34:15.230 --> 00:34:16.790What do you want a home for? 50000:34:16.870 --> 00:34:18.770For Miss Suellen and meto set up housekeeping. 50100:34:23.710 --> 00:34:25.570Here in Atlanta. You'd want to bring herto Atlanta, wouldn't you? 50200:34:25.640 --> 00:34:27.510There wouldn't be much helpin that for Tara. 50300:34:27.580 --> 00:34:30.700I don't rightly know what you mean,Miss Scarlett. 50400:35:03.950 --> 00:35:06.570I don't mean a thing. 50500:35:06.650 --> 00:35:09.740Frank, how'd you like to drive me outto my Aunt Pitty's? 50600:35:10.390 --> 00:35:11.410Nothing would give memore pleasure, Miss Scarlett. 50700:35:11.820 --> 00:35:14.250You'd better stay to supper, too. 50800:35:14.920 --> 00:35:16.410I'm sure Aunt Pitty'd be agreeableand I'd like a good long visit with you. 50900:35:24.330 --> 00:35:27.460Oh, you act on me just like a tonic,Miss Scarlett. 51000:35:27.540 --> 00:35:29.660And will you tell me all the news... 51100:36:13.780 --> 00:36:15.150...all the news of Miss Suellen? 51200:36:15.820 --> 00:36:18.980What's the matter, Miss Scarlett? 51300:36:19.190 --> 00:36:20.490Miss Suellen's not ill, is she? 51400:36:22.320 --> 00:36:24.950Oh, no, no. 51500:36:26.030 --> 00:36:28.550I thought surely she had written you. 51600:36:28.630 --> 00:36:30.930I guess she was ashamed to write you. 51700:36:31.600 --> 00:36:34.260She should be ashamed. 51800:36:34.940 --> 00:36:36.400Oh, how awful to have such a mean sister. 51900:36:37.140 --> 00:36:39.230You must tell me, Miss Scarlett.Don't leave me on tenterhooks. 52000:36:40.580 --> 00:36:41.570Well, she's going to marryone of the county boys next month. 52100:36:41.910 --> 00:36:43.430She just got tired of waitingand was afraid she'd be an old maid and.... 52200:36:43.850 --> 00:36:46.410Oh, I'm sorry to be the one to tell you. 52300:36:48.750 --> 00:36:50.120Oh, it's colder. I left my muff at home. 52400:36:50.190 --> 00:36:54.350Would you mindif I put my hand in your pocket? 52500:36:54.890 --> 00:36:57.520But, Melanie, you don't realizewhat she's done. 52600:36:57.690 --> 00:36:59.180She's gone and married my Mr. Kennedy. 52700:36:59.260 --> 00:37:01.200He's my beau,and she's gone and married him. 52800:37:01.330 --> 00:37:05.160She did it to save Tara,you must understand that. 52900:37:05.730 --> 00:37:07.460I hate Tara! 53000:37:08.440 --> 00:37:10.410And I hate Scarlett! She's the only thingI hate worse than Tara. 53100:37:10.470 --> 00:37:11.630It's all my fault. 53200:37:11.710 --> 00:37:13.770I should have committed highway robberyto get that tax money for you. 53300:37:14.010 --> 00:37:15.770I couldn't let you doanything like that, and.... 53400:37:15.840 --> 00:37:18.040Well, anyway, it's done now. 53500:37:18.110 --> 00:37:21.080Yes, it's done now. 53600:37:22.020 --> 00:37:23.180You wouldn't let medo anything dishonorable... 53700:37:23.620 --> 00:37:24.750...but you'd sell yourself in marriageto a man you didn't love. 53800:37:25.490 --> 00:37:26.720Well, at least you won't have to worryabout my helplessness anymore. 53900:37:26.790 --> 00:37:29.920What do you mean? 54000:37:29.990 --> 00:37:31.360I'm going to New York. 54100:37:31.890 --> 00:37:35.160I've arranged to get a positionin a bank there. 54200:37:36.970 --> 00:37:38.630But you can't do that. 54300:37:39.300 --> 00:37:41.500I counted on you to help me starta lumber business, Ashley... 54400:37:41.900 --> 00:37:43.800...and, well, I counted on you. 54500:37:46.940 --> 00:37:47.930I wouldn't be any good to you. 54600:37:48.240 --> 00:37:51.610I don't know anythingabout the lumber business. 54700:37:51.680 --> 00:37:53.150You know as much as you doabout banking. 54800:37:53.220 --> 00:37:56.650And I'd give you half the business, Ashley. 54900:37:56.720 --> 00:37:58.580That's generous of you, Scarlett. 55000:37:58.650 --> 00:38:01.250But it isn't that. 55100:38:01.320 --> 00:38:04.820If I go to Atlantaand take help from you again... 55200:38:25.850 --> 00:38:28.650...l'd bury forever any hopeof standing alone. 55300:38:28.780 --> 00:38:30.620Oh, is that all? 55400:38:30.690 --> 00:38:35.320Well, you could gradually buy the businessand then it would be your own, and.... 55500:38:35.490 --> 00:38:39.220No, Scarlett. 55600:38:39.390 --> 00:38:42.020Ashley.... 55700:38:42.100 --> 00:38:46.330Ashley. 55800:38:46.400 --> 00:38:49.460Scarlett! 55900:38:49.610 --> 00:38:51.330Scarlett, what is it? 56000:38:51.410 --> 00:38:54.900Ashley's so mean and hateful. 56100:39:07.260 --> 00:39:08.990What have you done? 56200:39:09.060 --> 00:39:11.750She wanted me to go to Atlanta. 56300:39:12.130 --> 00:39:15.220To help me start my lumber business, andhe won't lift a finger to help me, and he.... 56400:39:15.960 --> 00:39:19.090Why, how unchivalrous of you. 56500:39:19.270 --> 00:39:23.260Why, think, Ashley, think. 56600:39:32.380 --> 00:39:35.510If it hadn't been for Scarlett,I'd have died in Atlanta. 56700:39:35.980 --> 00:39:40.110And maybe we wouldn't have hadlittle Beau, and... 56800:39:40.490 --> 00:39:43.890...and when I think of her picking cottonand plowing just to keep food... 56900:39:44.130 --> 00:39:47.960...in our mouths, I could just.... 57000:39:48.160 --> 00:39:52.220Oh, my darling. 57100:39:52.430 --> 00:39:55.230All right, Melanie. 57200:39:55.540 --> 00:39:57.100I'll go to Atlanta. 57300:40:18.060 --> 00:40:19.460I can't fight you both. 57400:40:23.770 --> 00:40:26.960Well, here's your new mill hands,Mrs. Kennedy. 57500:40:27.270 --> 00:40:29.290The pick of all the best jails in Georgia. 57600:40:29.400 --> 00:40:31.630They look pretty thin and weak to me,Gallegher. 57700:40:32.040 --> 00:40:34.670Halt! 57800:40:34.740 --> 00:40:36.840They're the best you can lease, ma'am. 57900:40:37.110 --> 00:40:39.740And if you'll just give Johnny Galleghera free hand... 58000:40:39.820 --> 00:40:41.720...you'll get what you want out of them. 58100:40:42.820 --> 00:40:45.250All right, you're the foreman. 58200:40:45.320 --> 00:40:49.120All I ask is, you keep the mill runningand deliver my lumber when I want it. 58300:40:49.420 --> 00:40:51.480Johnny Gallegher's your man, Miss. 58400:40:51.560 --> 00:40:52.820But remember... 58500:40:53.430 --> 00:40:55.790...no questions and no interference. 58600:40:56.830 --> 00:40:58.160That's a bargain.Start them in the morning, Gallegher. 58700:40:58.470 --> 00:41:00.090Come on, get a move on!Come on, move on there! 58800:41:03.170 --> 00:41:05.200But, Scarlett, this isn't rightand you know it. 58900:41:05.340 --> 00:41:08.640It's bad enough for a womanto be in business, but-- 59000:41:09.280 --> 00:41:10.400What are you complaining about? 59100:41:12.880 --> 00:41:15.440You wouldn't have owned a millhad I not taken over. 59200:41:15.950 --> 00:41:17.010I didn't want the mill,and we couldn't have bought it... 59300:41:17.290 --> 00:41:19.850...if you hadn't pressed all of our friendsfor the money they owed me. 59400:41:22.120 --> 00:41:25.990Isn't that right, Ashley? 59500:41:26.290 --> 00:41:27.660What are you running,a charitable institution? 59600:41:27.730 --> 00:41:30.060Go back to the store,then go home and take your medicine. 59700:41:30.130 --> 00:41:32.660You're not looking very well. 59800:41:33.370 --> 00:41:35.360But, sugar, shouldn't you come homewith me? 59900:41:37.210 --> 00:41:40.870Great balls of fire. Don't bother meanymore, and don't call me sugar! 60000:41:41.140 --> 00:41:42.300All right, all right. 60100:41:42.380 --> 00:41:45.570Good night, Ashley. 60200:41:48.450 --> 00:41:49.920She can get mad quickerthan any woman I ever saw. 60300:41:49.990 --> 00:41:54.150Scarlett, I don't like to interfere, but... 60400:41:55.860 --> 00:41:59.590...l do wish you'd let me hire free darkiesinstead of using convicts. 60500:41:59.660 --> 00:42:03.290I believe we could do better. 60600:42:03.370 --> 00:42:06.860Darkies! Why, their pay would break us,and convicts are dirt cheap. 60700:42:06.940 --> 00:42:08.990If we just give Gallegher a free hand-- 60800:42:09.300 --> 00:42:10.530A free hand! You know what that means.He'll starve them and whip them. 60900:42:10.610 --> 00:42:12.660Some of them are sick, underfed.... 61000:42:13.140 --> 00:42:15.110Oh, Ashley, how you do run on. 61100:42:15.180 --> 00:42:17.610Left alone, you'd be giving them chickenthree times a day and... 61200:42:17.880 --> 00:42:19.740...tucking them to sleepwith eiderdown quilts. 61300:42:22.820 --> 00:42:24.790Scarlett, I will not make money outof the enforced labor and misery of others. 61400:42:24.890 --> 00:42:27.860You weren't so particularabout owning slaves. 61500:42:29.620 --> 00:42:33.750That was different.We didn't treat them that way. 61600:42:34.060 --> 00:42:35.790Besides, I'd have freed them allwhen father died... 61700:42:37.300 --> 00:42:40.360...if the war hadn't already freed them. 61800:42:40.440 --> 00:42:42.060Oh, I'm sorry, Ashley. 61900:42:42.140 --> 00:42:44.700But have you forgottenwhat it's like without money? 62000:42:45.070 --> 00:42:46.700I found out that money isthe most important thing in the world... 62100:42:46.810 --> 00:42:49.610...and I don't intend ever to bewithout it again. 62200:42:49.680 --> 00:42:50.940I'll make enough so the Yankees can nevertake Tara away from me. 62300:42:51.010 --> 00:42:54.040I'll make it the only way I know how. 62400:42:54.420 --> 00:42:55.580But we're not the only Southernerswho have suffered. 62500:42:55.720 --> 00:42:58.050Look at all our friends. They're keepingtheir honor and their kindness, too. 62600:42:58.250 --> 00:43:00.850And they're starving. I've got no usefor fools who won't help themselves. 62700:43:02.090 --> 00:43:04.890I know what they're saying about me,and I don't care. 62800:43:05.830 --> 00:43:07.490I'll make friendswith the Yankee carpetbaggers. 62900:43:08.300 --> 00:43:12.200And I'll beat them at their own game,and you'll beat them with me. 63000:43:12.330 --> 00:43:14.530That's it. Move it a little over to that side. 63100:43:14.600 --> 00:43:16.730Afternoon, Mrs. Kennedy. 63200:43:16.870 --> 00:43:18.930Good afternoon. 63300:43:19.470 --> 00:43:20.670Business is certainly growing, ain't it? 63400:43:20.780 --> 00:43:22.740It certainly is. 63500:43:25.650 --> 00:43:26.740But you're doing businesswith the same people who robbed us... 63600:43:27.120 --> 00:43:28.670...and tortured us and left us to starve. 63700:43:28.880 --> 00:43:31.050All that's past, Melly. 63800:43:31.150 --> 00:43:33.920And I intend to make the best of things,even if they are Yankee things. 63900:43:33.990 --> 00:43:37.450And do you know, Dolly Merriwether,that Dr. Meade actually saw her... 64000:43:38.260 --> 00:43:40.460...peddling lumberto those Yankees, herself. 64100:43:40.700 --> 00:43:42.030And that isn't all.... 64200:43:54.280 --> 00:43:57.510I think it's shocking what she's doingto my brother, Ashley. 64300:43:58.580 --> 00:44:00.610She's even taken to driving her own buggy. 64400:44:00.680 --> 00:44:02.450My dear Mrs. Kennedy. 64500:44:02.680 --> 00:44:03.710My very dear Mrs. Kennedy. 64600:44:03.850 --> 00:44:05.840I don't see how you havethe gall to face me. 64700:44:05.920 --> 00:44:07.680When I think you could have hadmy millions... 64800:44:07.760 --> 00:44:09.250...if you'd just waited a little while. 64900:44:09.320 --> 00:44:12.350Oh, how fickle is woman! 65000:44:44.190 --> 00:44:46.790What is it you want?I have important things to do. 65100:44:46.860 --> 00:44:49.060Would you satisfy my curiosity on a pointwhich has bothered me for some time? 65200:44:49.130 --> 00:44:51.160Well, what is it? Be quick. 65300:44:59.210 --> 00:45:01.470Tell me, Scarlett, do you never shrinkfrom marrying men you don't love? 65400:45:01.710 --> 00:45:05.510How did you ever get out of jail?Why didn't they hang you? 65500:45:05.650 --> 00:45:07.880Oh, that! Not much trouble. 65600:45:08.420 --> 00:45:09.710There's nothing muchthat money won't buy. 65700:45:10.490 --> 00:45:14.850I observe it's even bought youthe honorable Mr. Wilkes. 65800:45:15.720 --> 00:45:17.250So you still hate Ashley Wilkes. 65900:45:17.330 --> 00:45:20.160Do you know,I believe you're jealous of him. 66000:45:20.530 --> 00:45:21.690You still think you're the belleof the county, don't you? 66100:45:22.230 --> 00:45:26.460That you're the cutest little trickin shoe leather. 66200:45:46.420 --> 00:45:48.750And that every man you meetis dying of love for you. 66300:45:49.320 --> 00:45:51.290Let me by! 66400:45:51.360 --> 00:45:55.090Don't be angry, Scarlett.Tell me, where are you going? 66500:46:03.000 --> 00:46:05.100To the mill, if it's any of your business. 66600:46:05.170 --> 00:46:07.110Through shantytown, alone? 66700:46:07.280 --> 00:46:10.370Haven't you been told it's dangerousto drive alone through all that riffraff? 66800:46:10.450 --> 00:46:13.900Don't worry about me. 66900:46:14.620 --> 00:46:17.350I can shoot straightif I don't have to shoot too far. 67000:46:17.420 --> 00:46:18.440What a woman! 67100:46:18.590 --> 00:46:23.850Could ya gimme a quarter? 67200:46:24.430 --> 00:46:27.520Let go of my horse! 67300:46:37.710 --> 00:46:39.040Hold this horse! 67400:46:39.970 --> 00:46:41.600Help! 67500:46:42.280 --> 00:46:43.540Help! 67600:46:43.610 --> 00:46:44.840Help! 67700:46:44.910 --> 00:46:48.180Miss Scarlett! 67800:46:53.520 --> 00:46:56.010Miss Scarlett, wait! Miss Scarlett! 67900:47:01.430 --> 00:47:04.490Miss Scarlett! It's Big Sam! 68000:47:05.400 --> 00:47:06.800Big Sam! 68100:47:07.370 --> 00:47:09.860Miss Scarlett! Wait! 68200:47:10.040 --> 00:47:12.800Sam! Sam! 68300:47:12.870 --> 00:47:14.140Is you hurt, Miss Scarlett?Did they hurt you? 68400:47:14.540 --> 00:47:16.670Don't you cry, Miss Scarlett.Big Sam'll get you out of this in a jiffy. 68500:47:16.750 --> 00:47:17.730Horse, make tracks! 68600:47:17.810 --> 00:47:20.470You get to Tara just as quick as you can,and stay there. 68700:47:20.550 --> 00:47:24.250I sure will.I's got enough of them carpetbaggers. 68800:47:24.320 --> 00:47:26.290Thank you, Mr. Frank.Goodbye, Miss Scarlett. 68900:47:26.420 --> 00:47:30.190Goodbye, Sam, and thank you. 69000:47:30.260 --> 00:47:32.660Scarlett, change your dress and go overto Miss Melly's for the evening. 69100:47:32.730 --> 00:47:35.320I've got to go to a political meeting. 69200:47:36.060 --> 00:47:38.760A political meeting! 69300:47:49.040 --> 00:47:50.810How can you go to a political meeting... 69400:47:52.250 --> 00:47:54.180...after what I've been throughthis afternoon? 69500:47:54.250 --> 00:47:55.940Oh, sugar! You're more scared than hurt. 69600:47:56.020 --> 00:47:57.350Nobody cares about me.You all act as though it was nothing at all. 69700:47:57.420 --> 00:48:00.350The men talk, talk, talkabout protecting our women... 69800:48:00.420 --> 00:48:03.080...and after what happened to me todayFrank has to go to a political meeting. 69900:48:03.160 --> 00:48:05.960And if it won't pain you too much,lndia Wilkes... 70000:48:06.460 --> 00:48:09.160...l'd be much obligedif you'll tell me why you're staring at me. 70100:48:09.230 --> 00:48:11.960Has my face gone green or something? 70200:48:12.300 --> 00:48:13.930It won't pain me! 70300:48:14.000 --> 00:48:16.200What happened this afternoon wasjust what you deserved! 70400:48:16.270 --> 00:48:18.570And if there was any justice,you'd have gotten worse. 70500:48:18.640 --> 00:48:21.200India, hush up! 70600:48:21.340 --> 00:48:23.070Let her talk, Melanie.She's always hated me! 70700:48:23.140 --> 00:48:26.240Ever since I took your brotheraway from her... 70800:48:26.310 --> 00:48:27.300...though she's too much of a hypocriteto admit it! 70900:48:27.380 --> 00:48:29.480If she thought anyone'd go for her... 71000:48:31.190 --> 00:48:34.490...she'd walk down the street naked! 71100:48:34.560 --> 00:48:35.890I do hate you! 71200:48:35.960 --> 00:48:37.950You've done all you couldto lower the prestige of decent people. 71300:48:38.260 --> 00:48:41.420Now you've endangered the livesof our men, because they-- 71400:50:02.880 --> 00:50:03.970India! 71500:50:04.050 --> 00:50:06.740I don't think we'd better say any more,or one of us will be saying too much. 71600:50:07.020 --> 00:50:09.810What's going on around herethat I don't know about? 71700:50:13.720 --> 00:50:17.090Somebody's comin' up the walk. 71800:50:17.760 --> 00:50:18.950Somebody that ain't Mr. Ashley. 71900:50:19.030 --> 00:50:21.290Will you hand me the pistol, please,Mrs. Meade? 72000:50:21.900 --> 00:50:23.730Whoever it is... 72100:50:23.800 --> 00:50:24.770...we know nothing. 72200:50:24.830 --> 00:50:27.060Where have they gone? 72300:50:27.140 --> 00:50:29.300You've got to tell me, Mrs. Wilkes.It's life or death! 72400:50:31.140 --> 00:50:35.130Don't tell him anything. He's a Yankee spy. 72500:50:42.580 --> 00:50:44.020Quickly, please! There may still be time. 72600:50:45.620 --> 00:50:47.450How did you know? 72700:50:48.420 --> 00:50:49.690I've been playing pokerwith two Yankee captains. 72800:50:51.060 --> 00:50:52.750They knew there'd be trouble tonight. 72900:50:52.830 --> 00:50:55.490They've sent their cavalry outto be ready for it. 73000:50:56.260 --> 00:50:58.960Your husband and his friends arewalking into a trap. 73100:50:59.570 --> 00:51:01.400Don't tell him! He's trying to trap you! 73200:51:02.440 --> 00:51:06.310Out the Decatur Road.The old Sullivan plantation. 73300:51:06.410 --> 00:51:07.810The house is burned.They're meeting in the cellar. 73400:51:07.880 --> 00:51:10.110I'll do what I can. 73500:51:10.180 --> 00:51:12.010What's all this about?lf you don't tell me, I'll go crazy! 73600:51:14.750 --> 00:51:17.880We thought it best not to tell you, Scarlett. 73700:51:18.020 --> 00:51:19.210But Ashley and Frank and the othershave gone to clean out those woods... 73800:51:19.450 --> 00:51:21.150...where you were attacked. 73900:51:21.220 --> 00:51:22.710It's what a great manyof our Southern gentlemen have had... 74000:51:22.790 --> 00:51:23.690...to do lately for our protection. 74100:51:23.760 --> 00:51:27.490And if they're captured, they'll be hanged,Scarlett! 74200:51:27.560 --> 00:51:31.260And it will be your fault! 74300:51:32.130 --> 00:51:35.660Another word,and you go out of this house, lndia! 74400:51:36.440 --> 00:51:37.770Scarlett did what she thoughtshe had to do. 74500:51:38.070 --> 00:51:41.200And our men are doingwhat they think they have to do. 74600:51:41.380 --> 00:51:43.340Frank! 74700:51:43.410 --> 00:51:47.580And Ashley! 74800:51:49.780 --> 00:51:51.310Oh, it isn't possible! 74900:51:51.620 --> 00:51:55.060There's horses, Miss Melly.Here they come. 75000:51:55.390 --> 00:51:56.790You're sewing, you're sewing. 75100:52:33.530 --> 00:52:35.050Open the door, Mammy. 75200:52:38.470 --> 00:52:41.440Good evening, Mrs. Kennedy. 75300:52:41.740 --> 00:52:43.930Which of you ladies is Mrs. Wilkes? 75400:52:44.140 --> 00:52:46.540I am Mrs. Wilkes. 75500:52:50.480 --> 00:52:52.540I should like to speak to Mr. Wilkes,if you please. 75600:52:54.050 --> 00:52:55.350He's not here. 75700:52:57.790 --> 00:53:01.550Are you sure? 75800:53:01.890 --> 00:53:03.410Don't you doubt Miss Melly's word. 75900:53:06.730 --> 00:53:08.420I meant no disrespect, Mrs. Wilkes. 76000:53:17.040 --> 00:53:20.840If you'll give me your word,I won't search the house. 76100:53:21.410 --> 00:53:23.340Search if you like, but Mr. Wilkes is ata political meeting at Mr. Kennedy's store. 76200:53:23.510 --> 00:53:26.640He's not at the store,and there's no meeting tonight! 76300:53:27.180 --> 00:53:28.240No political meeting. 76400:53:28.520 --> 00:53:32.920We'll wait outsidetill he and his friends return. 76500:53:32.990 --> 00:53:34.320Sergeant, surround the house.Put a man on each door and window. 76600:53:35.060 --> 00:53:36.050Yes, sir! 76700:53:36.760 --> 00:53:38.820Keep on with your sewing, ladies. 76800:53:38.990 --> 00:53:41.390And I'll read aloud. 76900:53:43.870 --> 00:53:46.200"The Personal History and Experienceof David Copperfield. 77000:53:46.270 --> 00:53:49.960"Chapter one. 77100:53:50.040 --> 00:53:51.530"l'm born. 77200:53:51.610 --> 00:53:54.040"To begin my life, with the beginningof my