 --> 00:55:44.410...and try to remembernot to come here again? 80200:55:45.090 --> 00:55:47.920Well, now that's fine thanks I getfor bringing him home... 80300:55:54.930 --> 00:55:56.900...and not leaving him on the streetsin this shameful condition! 80400:55:57.800 --> 00:55:59.530Now, boys, all together! 80500:56:00.800 --> 00:56:04.670Dr. Meade... 80600:56:05.070 --> 00:56:06.330...l'm astonished at you! 80700:56:07.380 --> 00:56:10.210Oh, Ashley! How can you do this to me? 80800:56:10.580 --> 00:56:13.640I ain't so very drunk, Melly. 80900:56:14.450 --> 00:56:16.440Take him into the bedroomand lay him out on the bed as usual. 81000:56:16.580 --> 00:56:17.640Don't touch him, he's under arrest! 81100:56:18.050 --> 00:56:20.110Now, Tom. 81200:56:21.260 --> 00:56:24.320What do you want to arrest him for? 81300:56:24.790 --> 00:56:26.160I've seen him drunker. 81400:56:26.230 --> 00:56:29.860I've seen you drunker!And you've seen me.... 81500:56:30.100 --> 00:56:31.620He can lie in the gutter for all I care!I'm not a policeman. 81600:56:32.670 --> 00:56:36.030But he led a raid tonighton that shantytown... 81700:56:36.340 --> 00:56:37.300...where Mrs. Kennedy got into troublethis afternoon. 81800:56:37.370 --> 00:56:38.840A lot of those shanties were burned.A couple of men were killed. 81900:56:39.640 --> 00:56:41.510It's about time you rebels learned you can'ttake the law into your own hands. 82000:56:42.940 --> 00:56:45.910What are you laughing at? 82100:56:45.980 --> 00:56:48.680This isn't your nightto teach that lesson, Tom. 82200:56:49.850 --> 00:56:52.220These two have beenwith me tonight. Yes, sir. 82300:56:52.950 --> 00:56:54.420With you, Rhett? 82400:56:54.860 --> 00:56:59.190Where? 82500:57:02.200 --> 00:57:04.930I don't like to say in the presence of ladies. 82600:57:05.900 --> 00:57:08.390You'd better say. 82700:57:09.500 --> 00:57:11.630Come out on the porch and I'll tell you. 82800:57:14.080 --> 00:57:15.060Speak out, Captain Butler! 82900:57:16.480 --> 00